occurrenceRemarks: Under and between clumps of low shrubs, not seen in open barren rocky areas. Heavy fleshy taproot, or 2-3; squat to ground and none more than 5 cm above surface. Spines whitish. Plants dug and planted in garden at Las Barracas, BCS. Fls. and frts. collected from these cultivated plants on subsequent dates (on packets). Fls. (4/5/86) pink, c. 3.5 cm across, widely open. The entire pistil about as long as the inner petals with the 8 distinctly yellow stigma lobes extending beyond the petals in mature closed flowers. Style very pale pink. 4/27/86: fls. 3.2-4.5 cm diam. 4/28/86: fls. not yet open at 10:00 AM on overcast day, but 2A and 4B had opened by 8:00 AM.
locality: 1 km north of Santa Rosaliita schoolhouse, c. 1-2 km inland along dirt road north long the coast

verbatimAttributes: Plantas arbustivas, 0.80 m de alto, 1.2m de ancho; ramas erectas 3-4 segmentos de alto. Segmentos del tallo obovados, 15-18 cm de largo, 10-12 cm ancho, 1.5 cm de grueso, con 6-7 series de areolas, distantes entre si 1.5 cm.Areolas elipticas, ligeramente elevadas, 4 mm de largo, 3 mm de ancho. Gloquidas dispuestas en mechon apical, Amarillo obscure a dorados, en la mitad superior de la areola. Espnas aciculares, la base plana, blancas; las radials 1-3, depresas a ascendentes, 1.5-2.5 cm de largo, una mas larga que las otras; espina central ascendente a erecta, 1, 2.5-5 cm de largo, flexibles, el apice obscure, ligeramnete curvas. Frutos obovados, rojizos al madurar, 2.5- 3.5 cm de largo, 1.5-2.5 cm de diametro; espinosos, con espinas ascendentes a depresas; areolas 2-3 mm de largo, con gloquidas Amarillo obscure; las espinas blancas, aciculares, el apice mas onscuro. Cicatriz floral 1.25 cm de diametro; 1.0 cm de profundidad; las paredes del pericarpio 0.5 cm grueso, la cavidad 1.25-1.5 cm de ancho, carnosos, con sabor acido. Semillas numerosas, aplanadas, 4 mm de diametro.
associatedTaxa: Encelia farinosa, Prosopis velutina, Acacia cochliacantha, Lycium sp, Phaulothamnus sp, Opuntia setispina, Cylindropuntia kleiniae, C. fulgida, C. thurberi, Parkinsonia praecox, Jatropha cardiophylla y Agave angustifolia,.
locality: En camino Sahuaripa a Reserva Los Pavos ca. de 24.5 km al NNE de Sahuaripa.

occurrenceRemarks: Common on dunes at back of beach, forming thickets c. 2 m tall. Live material collected c. 1989 and now cultivated: Lubinsky residence, Redlands Blvd. near Anderson Street, Loma Linda, CA. Shrubby and 1.0-1.5 m (4-5pads) tall; flowers yellow, filaments greenish-white; style thick, pink; stigma light green (not white). Ripe fruits purplish-red, juicy, with a few spines at the base. Pads slightly glaucous, mostly green; margins often conspicuously undulate. Areoles elevated; surrounded by a ring of short pinkish (not white) wool. Spines yellow, few, many areoles with none, others with 1-2, very sparse on younger pads, mostly on older. Leaves quickly deciduous, slightly curved backward.
locality: Bahia Campeche near Isla de Carmen

verbatimAttributes: Erect shrub, about 1.0 x 1.3o m, openly branched, short definite trunk; growing under shade of Quercus and Cupressus associated to O. pahaeacantha. Flower bright yellow at anthesis truning dark yellow to orange, 8 cm long by 8-10 cm wide; ovary club shaped, 5.5-6.0 cm long by 2.0-3.0 cm wide at upper part, with 3 spiralated series of areoloes; areoles 1.2-1.7 cm apart, circular, 2-3 mm diam, with brownish wool and glochids yellow to dark brown, short; leaves present in upper areoles, conical to subulate, 7-10 mm long; external segments of perianth green with yellow edges, entire, deltoid to broadly obovate, apex mucronate, 8-32 mm long by 8-22 mm wide; inner segments bright yellow, spatulate to obovate, undulate, 30-40 mm long by 14-25 mm wide; filaments white with green base, the lower ones 12 mm long; anthers 2-2.5 mm long, style white-yellow, 18 mm long by 6 mm wide; stigma 10 lobes, 7-9 mm long, light green.  Fruit steril, persistent, parasited by wasp, no seed formed

verbatimAttributes: Arbustos erectos con tronco definido a postrados, 1-130 m de alto, 1-2.0 m de ancho; tronco con pelos cerdosos, blancos cubriendo las areolas. Segmentos del tallo aorbiculares a anchamente obovados, 12-15 cm largo, 10-13 cm ancho. Areolas ellipticas, 5-8 mm long, 4-5 mm ancho; gloquidas en toda la superficie de la areola, amarillo obscuro, 3-6 mm de largo. Espinas subuladas, 3--6 (-9), la mayoria en parte media superior de la penca, amarillas con base obscura. Todas las plantulas encontradas presentan los pelos blancos cubriendo las areolas. Plantulas de hasta 20 cm de altura presentan los pelos y despues desarrollan pencas orbiculares sin pelos en las areolas. Plantas maduras presentan pelos en el tronco.
